   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Hey! So there isn't an SSH account for Mailman right now, but I can work on
giving you access.

The easy way that I was originally thinking was to modify the Mailman signup
page's HTML -- just remove the comment form stuff, and/or add custom CSS to hide
it from the user. Then we don't prompt them for a password.

Mailman will email them a password for mailman, and that's that.

We could also Django-auth-ify it. That would be intriguing.

Either way, next step is giving you access. Therefore I'll assign it to me.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
