  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>I've looked at the sections of the Mailman code referenced in the message below,
and there is a nice system for authenticating against a different database (like
pretty much every system has) via replacing the default
Mailman/OldStyleMemberships.py. However, as with MediaWiki and Roundup, this
only affects the authentication back-end, not the fact that we allow
authentication via OpenID or username/password on Django; hence I foresee some
interface and authentication process hacking, since Mailman doesn't seem to have
any sort of plugin interface.

Asheesh, is there an SSH account for Mailman like there is for the bug tracker,
wiki, sufjan etc. that I could get access to?</pre>
   </td>
